{"type":"message","id":"fc28e689","parentId":"a662895d","timestamp":"2026-07-05T17:31:38.987Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_956d8c94360241c8a411a69b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"            enabled = \"true\"\r\n            level_str = dss_level\r\n        xml_str = '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>' + chr(10) + '<DSS version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">' + chr(10) + '  <enabled>' + enabled + '</enabled>' + chr(10) + '  <DSSLevel>' + level_str + '</DSSLevel>' + chr(10) + '</DSS>'\r\n        put_resp = client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/DSS\", xml_str)\r\n        if put_resp.status_code == 200:\r\n            log_info(\"image\", \"dss\", {\"device\": device_id, \"level\": dss_level})\r\n            try:\r\n                mac_clean = device_id.replace(\":\", \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\").lower()\r\n                if len(mac_clean) == 12:\r\n                    save_device_settings(mac_clean, {\"slow_shutter\": {\"dss_level\": dss_level, \"enabled\": dss_level != \"off\"}})\r\n            except Exception:\r\n                pass\r\n            return {\"success\": True, \"message\": \"慢快门: \" + (\"关闭\" if dss_level == \"off\" else dss_level)}\r\n        return {\"success\": False, \"message\": f\"设置失败: HTTP {put_resp.status_code}\"}\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n\n[546 more lines in file. Use offset=3825 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783272698987}}
{"type":"message","id":"22fef351","parentId":"fc28e689","timestamp":"2026-07-05T17:32:31.715Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the current state and what needs to be done:\n\n1. The current save mechanism in router.py already saves settings after each PUT endpoint succeeds (whitebalance, noisereduce, exposure, shutter, iris, sharpness, slow_shutter, image_settings)\n2. The problem is that during whitebalance/autofocus search (框选白平衡/框选自动对焦), the search process makes many steps, and we need to save ONLY after the search completes, not during each step.\n\nLet me look at what happens during the whitebalance and autofocus search:\n- whitebalance.py: `WhiteBalanceSearcher.run()` - does WB search, at the end it sets gains and locks mode\n- autofocus.py: `FocusSearcher.run()` - does focus search, at the end it stops\n\nThe key issue: During WB search, the process calls `_set_wb_gains()` many times (each step). If each of these triggers a save via the router's PUT endpoint, that's excessive I/O.\n\nWait, let me re-read. The WB search in whitebalance.py calls `_set_wb_gains()` directly via ISAPI client, NOT through the router API. So the router's save_device_settings is NOT called during each step.\n\nLet me check what the actual problem is. The user said:\n\"在画面控制-区域，也就是框选白平衡和框选自动对焦的时候，过程中有大量的调用，我需要在整个对焦或白平衡结束之后，执行一次保存\"\n\nSo the issue is:\n1. During WB search, `_set_wb_gains()` is called many times directly via ISAPI\n2. After the search completes, the final R/B gains and WB mode need to be saved\n3. During focus search, focus mode changes happen, and after completion, focus mode needs to be saved\n\nCurrently, the WB search in whitebalance.py:\n- Calls `_set_wb_mode(\"manual\")` at start\n- Calls `_set_wb_gains()` many times during search\n- At end, calls `_set_wb_mode(\"locked\")` \n- Does NOT save anything to settings.json\n\nThe focus search in autofocus.py:\n- Calls `_set_manual_focus()` at start\n- Does NOT save anything to settings.json\n\nSo the fix is:\n1. After WB search completes (in `run()` method), save the final WB settings (mode=locked, red_gain, blue_gain)\n2. After focus search completes (in `run()` method), save the focus settings\n\nBut wait - the user said \"保存设备当前配置，是整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照\". This means we need to save ALL settings as a snapshot, not just the ones that changed.\n\nLet me re-read the requirements:\n1. Save ALL settings (except PTZ movement and PTZ position) as a snapshot\n2. Save should be async, reduce overhead - save once after WB/focus completes, not each step\n3. No new scripts, no new files, only modify existing code\n\nSo the approach should be:\n1. In device_settings.py: Add a function to capture a full snapshot of all current device settings\n2. In whitebalance.py: After WB search completes, call a save function\n3. In autofocus.py: After focus search completes, call a save function\n4. The save function should capture ALL current settings from the device and save them\n\nWait, but the user also said \"router.py只提供端点的路由。保存和读取的具体工作由device_settings.py完成\". So the save logic should be in device_settings.py.\n\nLet me think about what \"full snapshot\" means:\n- Read all current settings from the device via ISAPI\n- Save them to settings.json\n- This should be done asynchronously\n\nBut the user said \"禁止硬编码，包括设备的MAC、IP、型号等\". So we need to pass MAC properly.\n\nLet me look at how the WB/focus searchers get the device info. They have `self.mgr`, `self.device_ip`, and `self.client`.\n\nThe MAC can be derived from the device_ip by looking up the controller.\n\nActually, let me re-read more carefully. The user's requirements:\n\n1. \"保存设备当前配置，是整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照\" - Save ALL settings as a snapshot\n2. \"保存中，需要异步，需要降低占用\" - Async, reduce overhead\n3. \"在画面控制-区域，也就是框选白平衡和框选自动对焦的时候，过程中有大量的调用，我需要在整个对焦或白平衡结束之后，执行一次保存\" - Save once after WB/focus completes\n4. \"禁止开发新脚本，禁止引入新脚本\" - No new scripts\n5. \"需要完整修复所有的关联，禁止硬编码\" - Fix all associations, no hardcoding\n\nAnd the user's clarifications:\n1. \"router.py只提供端点的路由。保存和读取的具体工作由device_settings.py完成\" - Save/read in device_settings.py\n2. \"需要完整修复所有的关联，禁止硬编码，包括设备的MAC、IP、型号等\" - No hardcoding MAC/IP/model\n3. \"绝对禁止随手改其他代码，只修复绝对需求的部分和依赖的部分\" - Only modify what's needed\n4. \"保存工作不包含任何图片，只包含运行完毕之后，定档的R B白平衡数值、白平衡模式、对焦模式\" - Save only: R/B WB values, WB mode, focus mode\n5. \"备份后迭代版本号，分步执行\" - Backup first, then version bump, then execute step by step\n\nWait, point 4 is interesting. The user says the save should only include:\n- R/B whitebalance values (red_gain, blue_gain)\n- Whitebalance mode\n- Focus mode\n\nBut earlier they said \"整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照\". These seem contradictory.\n\nLet me re-read: \"关于你的问题，删除重复截图，保存工作不包含任何图片，只包含运行完毕之后，定档的R B白平衡数值、白平衡模式、对焦模式。\"\n\nI think the user is saying: for the WB/focus search completion save, only save these specific values (not a full snapshot). The \"full snapshot\" in requirement 1 might refer to the general save mechanism (which already exists in router.py for each endpoint).\n\nSo the actual fix needed:\n1. After WB search completes → save final R/B gains + WB mode (locked)\n2. After focus search completes → save focus mode\n\nBut we also need to handle the \"full snapshot\" requirement. Let me think...\n\nActually, re-reading requirement 1 again: \"我需要的，保存设备当前配置，是整个astrohub主控台上所有设置的快照，所有可以操作的设置，除了手动PTZ运动控制，除了设备当前的PTZ位置，其他全都需要保存\"\n\nThis says: save ALL operable settings except manual PTZ movement and current PTZ position.\n\nAnd requirement 2 says: during WB/focus search, save once at the end, not each step.\n\nSo the \"full snapshot\" is about what gets saved, and the \"async/once at end\" is about when.\n\nBut then the user's clarification in point 4 says: \"保存工作不包含任何图片，只包含运行完毕之后，定档的R B白平衡数值、白平衡模式、对焦模式\"\n\nThis seems to narrow it down to just: R/B values, WB mode, focus mode.\n\nHmm, but that contradicts \"所有可以操作的设置\". Let me re-read the context...\n\nThe user said \"关于你的问题\" - this is answering my questions. They're saying the save after WB/focus completion should only include the final values (R/B, WB mode, focus mode), NOT screenshots/images.\n\nSo the full picture is:\n1. The EXISTING save mechanism (in router.py after each PUT) already handles saving individual settings when the user manually changes them via the UI\n2. The MISSING piece is: when WB/focus search completes automatically, the final values need to be saved\n3. The save should NOT include images, just the parameter values\n\nSo the fix is:\n1. In whitebalance.py: After WB search completes, save the final R/B gains and WB mode\n2. In autofocus.py: After focus search completes, save the focus mode\n3. The save should be done via device_settings.py (as per user's clarification)\n4. No hardcoding of MAC - need to derive MAC from device context\n\nNow, how to get the MAC in whitebalance.py and autofocus.py?\n\nLooking at the code:\n- `WhiteBalanceSearcher.__init__` has `self.mgr`, `self.device_ip`\n- `FocusSearcher.__init__` has `self.mgr`, `self.device_ip`\n\nThe MAC can be obtained from the device manager by looking up the device by IP.\n\nLet me check how to get MAC from IP in the existing code...\n\nIn router.py, the pattern is:\n```python\nmac_clean = device_id.replace(\":\", \"\").replace(\"-\", \"\").lower()\n```\n\nBut in whitebalance.py/autofocus.py, we have device_ip, not device_id/MAC.\n\nLet me check how the region_base.py or other modules handle this...\n\nActually, looking at the WB search flow:\n1. The search is initiated from the frontend\n2. The frontend calls an API endpoint in router.py\n3. router.py creates the WhiteBalanceSearcher with the device info\n\nLet me find where WhiteBalanceSearcher is instantiated in router.py.\n\nI need to search for where WhiteBalanceSearcher is created. Let me look at the router.py code more carefully.\n\nActually, I didn't see the WB/focus search endpoints in the router.py I read. Let me search for them.\n\nI need to read more of router.py to find the WB/focus search endpoints. Let me search for \"WhiteBalanceSearcher\" or \"FocusSearcher\" or \"whitebalance\" or \"autofocus\" in router.py.\n\nLet me also check what the current version is and plan the backup + version bump.\n\nCurrent version from HEARTBEAT.md: v8.46\nNext version: v8.47\n\nPlan:\n1. Backup the files that will be modified\n2. Bump version to v8.47\n3. Modify device_settings.py to add a function that saves WB/focus settings\n4. Modify whitebalance.py to call save after WB search completes\n5. Modify autofocus.py to call save after focus search completes\n6. Ensure MAC is passed correctly (no hardcoding)\n\nLet me first find where WhiteBalanceSearcher and FocusSearcher are instantiated.\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9fd38f89822d495484259546","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub && Select-String -Path src\\api\\router.py -Pattern \"WhiteBalanceSearcher|FocusSearcher|whitebalance_search|focus_search\" | ForEach-Object { \"$($_.LineNumber): $($_.Line.Trim())\" }"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ea56e18accb4461687f1dbb9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub && Select-String -Path src\\api\\router.py -Pattern \"region_wb|region_focus|area_wb|area_focus|框选\" | ForEach-Object { \"$($_.LineNumber): $($_.Line.Trim())\" }"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":39066,"output":2425,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41491,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783272698988,"responseId":"chatcmpl-e8b520d8-b131-92f7-a754-c28a43aa1742"}}
