{"type":"message","id":"cde9b58a","parentId":"1416833c","timestamp":"2026-07-05T17:34:12.377Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_OOwiz4Oj8nJ3sa3NJQ5N4738","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def get_connected_device(self) -> dict | None:\n        \"\"\"v7.10: ���� last_connected �豸��Ϣ�����ڿ������ӣ���\n        \n        ע�⣺�˷������ص���\"�ϴ����ӵ��豸\"����һ����\"��ǰ���ӵ��豸\"��\n        ǰ��Ӧ��ͨ����� IP �Ƿ��� _controllers ���ж��Ƿ�ʵ�����ӡ�\n        \"\"\"\n        import json\n        from src.config_paths import REGISTRY_FILE, DEVICES_DIR\n        \n        try:\n            # v7.10: ��ȡ last_connected�����ڿ������ӣ�\n            if REGISTRY_FILE.exists():\n                registry = json.loads(REGISTRY_FILE.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n                last_mac = registry.get('last_connected', '').strip()\n                \n                # last_connected Ϊ�ձ�ʾ��δ���ӹ�\n                if not last_mac:\n                    return None\n                \n                # �� devices/{mac}/info.json ��ȡ�豸����\n                info_file = DEVICES_DIR / last_mac / 'info.json'\n                if info_file.exists():\n                    info = json.loads(info_file.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n                    creds = info.get('credentials', {})\n                    return {\n                        'ip': info.get('ip'),\n                        'mac': last_mac,\n                        'name': info.get('name'),\n                        'model': info.get('model'),\n                        'username': creds.get('username') or info.get('username'),\n                        'password': creds.get('password') or info.get('password'),\r\n            print(f'[PTZDeviceController] get_connected_device error: {e}')\n        \n        return None\n\n    # ================================================================\n    #  �豸��Ϣ��ȡ\n    # ================================================================\n\n    def get_device_info(self, ip: str) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"ͨ�� ISAPI ��ȡ�豸��ϸ��Ϣ��\"\"\"\n        if ip not in self._clients:\n            # �����Զ�����\n            creds = self.get_credentials(ip)\n            if creds:\n                client = ISAPIClient(ip=ip, username=creds[\"username\"],\n                                     password=creds[\"password\"], port=creds.get(\"port\", 80))\n                if not client.verify_credentials():\n                    return {\"error\": \"��֤ʧ��\"}\n                self._clients[ip] = client\n                self._controllers[ip] = PTZController(client)\n            else:\n                return {\"error\": \"�豸δ��������ƾ��\"}\n\n        client = self._clients[ip]\n        info = {}\n\n        # ϵͳ��Ϣ\n        result = client.get(\"/System/deviceInfo\")\n        if result.status_code == 200:\n            try:\n                root = ET.fromstring(result.xml)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":451,"aggregated":"def get_connected_device(self) -> dict | None:\n        \"\"\"v7.10: ���� last_connected �豸��Ϣ�����ڿ������ӣ���\n        \n        ע�⣺�˷������ص���\"�ϴ����ӵ��豸\"����һ����\"��ǰ���ӵ��豸\"��\n        ǰ��Ӧ��ͨ����� IP �Ƿ��� _controllers ���ж��Ƿ�ʵ�����ӡ�\n        \"\"\"\n        import json\n        from src.config_paths import REGISTRY_FILE, DEVICES_DIR\n        \n        try:\n            # v7.10: ��ȡ last_connected�����ڿ������ӣ�\n            if REGISTRY_FILE.exists():\n                registry = json.loads(REGISTRY_FILE.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n                last_mac = registry.get('last_connected', '').strip()\n                \n                # last_connected Ϊ�ձ�ʾ��δ���ӹ�\n                if not last_mac:\n                    return None\n                \n                # �� devices/{mac}/info.json ��ȡ�豸����\n                info_file = DEVICES_DIR / last_mac / 'info.json'\n                if info_file.exists():\n                    info = json.loads(info_file.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n                    creds = info.get('credentials', {})\n                    return {\n                        'ip': info.get('ip'),\n                        'mac': last_mac,\n                        'name': info.get('name'),\n                        'model': info.get('model'),\n                        'username': creds.get('username') or info.get('username'),\n                        'password': creds.get('password') or info.get('password'),\r\n            print(f'[PTZDeviceController] get_connected_device error: {e}')\n        \n        return None\n\n    # ================================================================\n    #  �豸��Ϣ��ȡ\n    # ================================================================\n\n    def get_device_info(self, ip: str) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"ͨ�� ISAPI ��ȡ�豸��ϸ��Ϣ��\"\"\"\n        if ip not in self._clients:\n            # �����Զ�����\n            creds = self.get_credentials(ip)\n            if creds:\n                client = ISAPIClient(ip=ip, username=creds[\"username\"],\n                                     password=creds[\"password\"], port=creds.get(\"port\", 80))\n                if not client.verify_credentials():\n                    return {\"error\": \"��֤ʧ��\"}\n                self._clients[ip] = client\n                self._controllers[ip] = PTZController(client)\n            else:\n                return {\"error\": \"�豸δ��������ƾ��\"}\n\n        client = self._clients[ip]\n        info = {}\n\n        # ϵͳ��Ϣ\n        result = client.get(\"/System/deviceInfo\")\n        if result.status_code == 200:\n            try:\n                root = ET.fromstring(result.xml)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783272852377}}
{"type":"message","id":"f1244fbf","parentId":"cde9b58a","timestamp":"2026-07-05T17:34:25.448Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the structure of get_connected_device. It returns:\n- 'ip': info.get('ip')\n- 'mac': last_mac\n- 'name': info.get('name')\n- 'model': info.get('model')\n- 'username': creds.get('username')\n- 'password': creds.get('password')\n\nSo the connected dict contains 'mac'. This means I can use `connected['mac']` in router.py to pass to the searchers.\n\nNow let me plan the minimal changes:\n\n1. **router.py**: \n   - In `whitebalance_search()`: pass `mac_clean=connected['mac']` to WhiteBalanceSearcher\n   - In `focus_search()`: pass `mac_clean=connected['mac']` to FocusSearcher\n\n2. **whitebalance.py**:\n   - Add `mac_clean` parameter to `__init__`\n   - In `run()`, after the search completes (both done and interrupt cases), call `save_settings(mac_clean, {...})` to save:\n     - whitebalance mode: \"locked\"\n     - red_gain: final value\n     - blue_gain: final value\n\n3. **autofocus.py**:\n   - Add `mac_clean` parameter to `__init__`\n   - In `run()`, after the search completes, call `save_settings(mac_clean, {...})` to save:\n     - focus mode: \"manual\"\n\nLet me also check what the current focus mode is saved as in router.py to ensure consistency.\n\nFrom my earlier read of router.py, I saw that whitebalance is saved as:\n```python\nsave_device_settings(mac_clean, {\"whitebalance\": {\"mode\": mode_val, \"red_gain\": red_val, \"blue_gain\": blue_val}})\n```\n\nI need to check if there's a focus mode being saved anywhere. Let me search for it.\n\nActually, looking at the autofocus.py code, I see `_set_manual_focus()` which sets focus to MANUAL mode. But I haven't seen where focus mode is saved in router.py yet.\n\nLet me search for focus-related saves in router.py.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"完美！`get_connected_device()` 返回的 dict 包含 `mac` 字段。现在开始修改。\n\n先检查 autofocus.py