{"type":"message","id":"c8dc96ee","parentId":"f05a952d","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:05:59.901Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The comparison results show:\n\n1. backup_20260706_0032/src/api/router.py vs backup_20260706_0129/router.py: Only difference is `import json` appears twice in one of them (minor difference)\n2. Current router.py vs backup_20260706_0032/src/api/router.py:\n   - OSD/PTZ patterns: No differences\n   - Region/框选/analyze patterns: No differences\n\nSo the current router.py has the same OSD PTZ and region analysis code as the backup. The only differences are my v8.47 changes (focus mode save, mac_clean passing).\n\nWait, but the user said \"你给我把主控台的哪些修改都还原回来了？\" - meaning \"You restored all the modifications to the main control console?\"\n\nThis implies they think I overwrote some changes. But from the comparison, the only differences are:\n1. My v8.47 changes (which I intentionally added)\n2. Some `import json` duplication (minor)\n\nLet me think about this differently. Maybe the user is referring to changes that were made AFTER backup_20260706_0032 but BEFORE backup_20260706_0129. Or maybe they're referring to changes that were made in the current session but not backed up.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the user's message: \"卧槽你大爷的，你给我把主控台的哪些修改都还原回来了？找到之前备份，修改OSD PTZ信息开关、修改框选分析的部分，完全对比异同！\"\n\nThe user is saying:\n1. \"You restored all the modifications to the main control console?\"\n2. \"Find the previous backup, compare the OSD PTZ info switch and region analysis parts!\"\n\nThey want me to find what changes were made and then lost. But from the comparison, the current files match the backup (except for my intentional v8.47 changes).\n\nLet me check if there were any changes made in the current session that got overwritten. Actually, I didn't modify console.html at all. I only modified:\n- whitebalance.py\n- autofocus.py\n- router.py\n- constants.py\n\nSo the console.html (which likely contains the