{"type":"message","id":"58a68372","parentId":"90022c56","timestamp":"2026-07-05T18:40:10.348Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying I restored (reverted) the console.html that had slow shutter and other UI elements removed. They want me to find the version that HAS slow shutter HTML elements.\n\nLet me analyze what I've found:\n1. Current console.html (src/web/includes/console.html) has JS references to slowShutter but NO HTML select element\n2. backup_20260706_0032 (the v8.46 backup) also has NO slow shutter HTML\n3. All older backups don't have slow shutter at all\n4. Git history shows commits up to v7.37, but the versions are now v8.46+\n\nThe problem is: the slow shutter HTML was likely added in v8.45 or v8.46, but those commits may not have been made yet. The v8.45 work happened today (2026-07-05) according to HEARTBEAT.md, and the backup_20260706_0032 was created today.\n\nWait - let me re-read HEARTBEAT.md:\n- v8.46 设备参数记忆功能完成 (2026-07-05) - mentions 慢快门（DSS倍率）\n- v8.45 慢快门迁移DSS (2026-07-05) - mentions console.html changes for loadSlowShutter\n\nSo v8.45 DID add slow shutter to console.html! But the current console.html doesn't have it.\n\nThis means the console.html was reverted to an earlier version, losing the v8.45 changes.\n\nLet me check if there are uncommitted changes in git, or if I can find the v8.45 version somewhere.\n\nActually, looking at the backup_20260706_0032 which I created BEFORE my changes - it also doesn't have slow shutter HTML. This means the console.html was already reverted before I even started my work today.\n\nBut the user is saying I \"瞎恢复\" (blindly restored) it. Let me check what I actually did:\n1. I made backup_20260706_0129 which only contains 5 files (autofocus.py, constants.py, device_settings.py, router.py, whitebalance.py)\n2. I edited router.py, whitebalance.py, autofocus.py, constants.py\n\nI did NOT touch console.html at all!\n\nBut the user says I restored an older version. Let me check if there was a git operation that reverted files...\n\nActually, I should check the current git status and see if there are any uncommitted changes or if console.html differs from the backup.\n\nLet me also check if the v8.45 version of console.html exists somewhere else.\nLet me check if there are uncommitted changes and find the v8.45 version with slow shutter:\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_d1d4177831084771904fae68","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub && git status --short | Select-Object -First 20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_d7308a146bac466480460c84","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub && git log --oneline --all -- src/web/includes/console.html 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_6039e70280e342ea958fd8c1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub && git show HEAD:src/web/includes/console.html 2>&1 | Select-String -Pattern \"slowShutter|慢快门\" | Select-Object -First 5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_13c2e0835fc440faa53149c7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub && Select-String -Path backup_20260706_0032\\src\\web\\includes\\console.html -Pattern \"slowShutter|慢快门\" | Select-Object -First 5"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n</think>\n\nLet me check git log more carefully. The latest commit for console.html is v7.37 (b6ce5a5). But the current console.html file is from July 5 22:52, which suggests it was modified but not committed.\n\nLet me check what the actual current console.html has vs what it should have. The user says the current version was reverted and is missing:\n1. Slow shutter HTML element (only has JS references, no actual <select>)\n2. Three-stage switches\n\nLet me look at the actual HTML structure in the current console.html more carefully. Maybe there's a backup somewhere else.\n\nLet me check git status to see if there are uncommitted changes.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_d17d61c6381d4e08a9149533","name":"exec