{"type":"message","id":"125acd99","parentId":"46ec7fde","timestamp":"2026-07-05T19:04:58.832Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to continue checking the AstroHub console page. From the previous output, I can see that:\n\n1. The root URL `/` serves index.html\n2. The console page seems to be embedded in the index.html (not a separate route)\n3. The HTML includes references to \"console-layout\" CSS classes\n\nLet me check if the console is actually loaded via index.html and if the elements we added (slowShutterSelect, infoOsdSwitch, ptzOsdSwitch) are present in the served HTML.\n\nI need to:\n1. Fetch the actual HTML from the root URL\n2. Check if the elements are present\n3. Take a proper screenshot of the console page\n\nLet me update the script to use the correct URL and verify the elements.\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_d1181e0dcd2a45eeb0e1b10a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub && python -c \"\nimport requests\nresp = requests.get('http://127.0.0.1:10280/')\nhtml = resp.text\nprint('Status:', resp.status_code)\nprint('Length:', len(html))\nprint()\nprint('slowShutterSelect:', 'slowShutterSelect' in html)\nprint('infoOsdSwitch:', 'infoOsdSwitch' in html)\nprint('ptzOsdSwitch:', 'ptzOsdSwitch' in html)\nprint('restoreSettings:', 'restoreSettings' in html)\nprint('loadSlowShutter:', 'loadSlowShutter' in html)\nprint('setSlowShutter:', 'setSlowShutter' in html)\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":6,"output":355,"cacheRead":185800,"cacheWrite":5323,"totalTokens":191484,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783278287202,"responseId":"msg_ec1c9f70-d425-4cfe-92a2-8e872c59e60b"}}
