{"type":"message","id":"3fae77da","parentId":"e7b2e5d8","timestamp":"2026-07-05T19:10:48.948Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking two questions:\n1. What is the current shutter speed configuration?\n2. How does the main console's motion control read the shutter speed - is it from device response or somewhere else?\n\nLet me analyze the screenshot and code to answer this.\n\nFrom the screenshot I can see the motion control area on the left shows:\n- 快门: 1/25\n\nSo the current shutter speed shown is 1/25.\n\nNow I need to understand how this value is obtained. Let me check the code:\n\n1. The motion control area is on the left side of the console\n2. The shutter speed display in the motion control area\n\nLooking at the screenshot:\n- Left panel \"运动控制\" shows 快门: 1/25\n- Right panel \"画面控制\" shows 快门: 1/25 (dropdown)\n\nThese are two different places showing the same value. Let me understand how each gets the value.\n\nFor the motion control (left panel), I need to find the code that displays the shutter speed. This is likely in the `loadShutter` function or similar.\n\nLet me search the console.html for how the shutter speed is loaded in the motion control area.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"从截图看，**当前快门速度是 1/25**。\n\n让我检查运动控制区域的快门速度是如何"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_46abd27ac5d243289cf08101","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub && Select-String -Path \"src\\web\\includes\\console.html\" -Pattern \"loadShutter|快门|shutterSpeed|shutter.*val\" -Context 1,1 | Select-Object -First 30 | ForEach-Object { \"$($_.Context.PreContext -join '|')`n$($_.Line)`n$($_.Context.PostContext -join '|')\" } | Select-Object -First 50"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_2e0754aabd934b54a96524c0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub && Select-String -Path \"src\\api\\router.py\" -Pattern \"shutter.*get|GET.*shutter|ISAPI.*Shutter\" | ForEach-Object { \"L$($_.LineNumber): $($_.Line.Trim().Subst